cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a self-supervised approach for learning spatiotemporal features from unlabeled videos, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach involves a pretext task of predicting rotations, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed framework on action recognition, which is a task in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses deep neural networks for learning, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
